;; Accessing help documentation with COMMAND-D
;

; The best way to learn how to express yourself in SAL is to study
; examples and try to figure out what they do BEFORE you execute
; them. You can use COMMAND-D to lookup documentation on new words you
; encounter as you work through these tutorials. To use COMMAND-D
; first put your cursor on the word you are interested in and then
; press COMMAND-D. Try it in the example above on the words: begin
; between pick note list and print.

